This paper deals with multi-label learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on exploiting global and local label correlations, which are important in computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and cybersecurity (cs.CR). The approach proposed in the paper involves learning a latent label representation, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.CR.
